@node IRT
@toc main

 A baby could use IRT so it is simple ! Choose a Source icon and launch it on the left side of the window (you can also use the "Load Source" button and the "Load Source" menu). Do the same with the destination icon. Once done, just click on the "Install" button and it's all over.
 And if you made a mystake, the "Undo" button is here to help you :)

 I think that's all you need to know to make good use of Icon Replacement Tool.
 
@endnode
@node Installation
@toc main

 You just have to copy IRT directory where you want to fix it.

@endnode
